Ya know the saying ‘go big or go home’? Well, they’re referring to portabellas. This well-known variety is a relative of the white button and crimini mushroom, and port caps can measure up to 6 inches 🤯 in diameter. As the largest cultivated mushroom, portabellas are hearty, savory and meaty. Visit the link in bio to learn more about this show stealing fungi. 
.

2 tablespoons vegan butter
3/4 cup walnuts, toasted and finely chopped
1/3 cup panko breadcrumbs
2 tablespoons minced shallots
1/2 teaspoon fresh thyme
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
1/2 teaspoon dried oregano
1/2 teaspoon dried parsley
Salt and pepper to taste
12 large cremini mushrooms, cleaned, stems removed
Olive oil for drizzling

A simple yet stunning go-to cooking technique for this variety is to dry sauté in a hot skillet until the water releases and the edges brown, then add butter and seasonings. How to sauté mushrooms? 👇

1️⃣ Brush pan with oil or butter and heat on high.
2️⃣ Add a single layer of mushrooms to the pan.
3️⃣ Flip once browned & repeat on the other side. 
4️⃣ Remove from heat & season to taste.

Save this post for next time you need an easy way to cook mushrooms.

Grilled Steaky Mushroom Skewers and Smoky Seared Button’s 🍄🌱🔥🍄
 
Whether you’re a mushroom aficionado or simply seeking a whole food and flavorful meal or fun meal prep, this recipe has it all.  Follow along as I guide you through crafting this culinary masterpiece that’s sure to delight taste buds. For the full episode check out my You tube and recreate this savory harmony of tastes.  Oh and if you’re wanting to learn more about the uses and benefits of mushrooms check out the mushroom council website at www.mushroomcouncil.com for some great info about mushrooms!
 
Steaky Mushroom Skewers:
Ingredients:
20 medium-size or 485g Crimini Mushrooms (Brown Mushrooms), stems removed
2 TBS Steak Flavored Seasoning Blend (your favorite blend)
1 tsp cooking oil
1 tsp olive oil
Salt & Pepper, to taste
Instructions:
 
Preheat your grill or heat a cast iron pan or skillet on medium-high heat.
Oil the pan.
Thread the mushrooms onto skewers.
Sprinkle the steak flavored seasoning, salt, and pepper over the mushrooms.
Place the skewers on the hot pan or grill.
Optionally, place another weighted pan gently on top of the skewers to draw out moisture and create more surface area for grilling.
Cook on both sides for several minutes until nicely charred and cooked through.
Remove from the pan or grill and set aside.
 
Smoky Grilled Button Mushrooms:
Ingredients:
300g Medium size White Button mushrooms, sliced
2 TBS Pork flavored seasoning blend (your favorite kind)
3 TBS Olive Oil
1 tsp cooking oil
Salt & Pepper, to taste
 
Instructions:
In a large bowl, mix the sliced mushrooms with olive oil and the pork flavored seasoning blend.
Allow the mushrooms to marinate for 10-15 minutes.
Preheat your grill and place a cast iron pan on it until hot.
Add the cooking oil and then the marinated mushrooms.
Sear and sauté the mushrooms for several minutes until they are charred and flavorful
